
  <sn><md>### Biological Efficiency

**Biological efficiency** refers to how effectively an organism converts the **energy stored in food (glucose)** into **usable energy (ATP)** during respiration.
It is measured by comparing:

$$
\text{Biological Efficiency} = \frac{\text{Energy captured as ATP}}{\text{Total energy present in glucose}} \times 100
$$

The total energy stored in **1 mole of glucose = 686 kcal** (approx).
